The paper discusses a neural network with spiking neurons that can solve the L1-minimizing dictionary learning problem. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses learning rules that rely solely on synaptically local information, which is a topic that falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions sensory neural systems and information processing, which are topics that fall under the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of feedback synapses to create a pathway to turn non-local information into local ones, which is a topic that falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the encoding of error signals needed for learning, which is a topic that falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
